The article summarizes a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on September 2, 2010. The President is closely monitoring Hurricane Earl and has signed an emergency declaration for North Carolina. The President was briefed on the oil platform fire in the Gulf of Mexico. The talks on the Middle East peace process are ongoing, and the President is encouraged by the serious attitude of the leaders involved. There are still deep divisions to overcome, but the President believes in actively trying for peace. Press Secretary Gibbs also addressed questions about the economy, job numbers, and the President's focus on economic recovery. He mentioned that the economic team is considering targeted measures to continue the recovery and create an environment for private sector hiring. There was also discussion about the possibility of extending tax cuts and the President's involvement in the upcoming election. The briefing ended with questions about the President's beliefs and his plans for 9/11 commemorations.